article.headline: SE Louisiana 71, Texas Arlington 62
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Ricky Woods recorded his 16th double-double of the season with 21 points and 10 rebounds as Southeastern rallied from a 12-point deficit and defeated Texas-Arlington, 71-62, in a Southland Conference game Saturday night. Chris Lee added a career-high 18 points as Southeastern (14-11, 8-6 SLC) outscored Texas-Arlington (13-14, 6-8 SLC), 43-28, in the second half. Terry Bryant added 12 points as Southeastern remained in a fourth-place tie with Lamar heading into the final week of the season. Jarrett Howell led UTA with 22 points while Steven Thomas added 21.
